<h2>Asset Turnover</h2><br>
<form Name=AssetTurn>
<input type="text" name="AssetTurnover" style="background-color: white" size="10" maxlength="50" disabled/>
<a Title="Asset Turnover:
This represents how often assets turn over 
given sales in the balance sheet. Shows 
how productive your assets are.  The more
the better greater than 1."> <img height="25" width="25" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/af/Question_mark.png" /></a>

<h2>Recievables Turnover</h2>
<input type="text" name="RecTurnover" style="background-color: white" size="10" maxlength="50" disabled/>
<a Title="Recievables Turnover:
This number represents how many times recievables
turn a period of time.  If recievable turnover is
low you may have a cash flow problem. A low ratio 
implies the company should re-assess its credit
 policies in order to ensure the timely 
 collection of imparted credit that is not 
 earning interest for the firm."> <img height="25" width="25" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/af/Question_mark.png" /></a>

<h2>Average Days in Inventory</h2>
<input type="text" name="AvDayInv" style="background-color: white" size="10" maxlength="50" disabled/>
<a Title="Average Days in Inventory:
The average number of days it takes one piece of 
inventory to get out the warehouse.  The lower the
better depends on your type of business."> <img height="25" width="25" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/af/Question_mark.png" /></a>

<h2>Inventory Turnover</h2>
<input type="text" name="InvTurnover" style="background-color: white" size="10" maxlength="50" disabled/>
<a Title="Inventory Turnover:
This ratio should be compared against industry
 averages. A low turnover implies poor sales and,
 therefore, excess inventory. A high ratio implies
 either strong sales or ineffective buying.
High inventory levels are unhealthy because 
they represent an investment with a rate of 
return of zero. It also opens the company up
 to trouble should prices begin to fall."> <img height="25" width="25" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/af/Question_mark.png" /></a>

</form>
